If you look at the [home wiki page](https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/wiki#misc), there is a demo showing how to deal with the table when inside of jQuery UI tabs. Basically, the table needs to be updated because hidden elements have a zero-width ([demo](http://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/abkNM/6633/)):

```js
$("#tabs").tabs({
    activate: function (event, ui) {
        var $t = ui.newPanel.find('table');
        if ($t.length) {
            if ($t[0].config) {
                $t.trigger('applyWidgets');
            } else {
                $t.tablesorter({
                    theme: 'blue',
                    widgets: ["zebra", 'scroller'],
                    widgetOptions: {
                        scroller_fixedColumns: 1,
                        scroller_height: 300,
                        // scroll tbody to top after sorting
                        scroller_upAfterSort: true,
                        // pop table header into view while scrolling up the page
                        scroller_jumpToHeader: true
                    }
                });
            }
        }
    }
});
```

Hi Mottie,

Thanks for tablesorter, it's great. I was running into problems with ISO 8601 sorting as well and found this bug. However, your update didn't actually resolve it for me. Here's the updated parser that I created that works for me.

```javascript
    ts.addParser({
        id: "isoDate",
        is: function(s) {
            return (/^\d{4}[\/\-]\d{1,2}[\/\-]\d{1,2}T\d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2}[\+,\-]\d{2}:\d{2}/).test(s);
        },
        format: function(s, table) {
            return ts.formatFloat((s !== "") ? (new Date(s).getTime() || "") : "", table);
        },
        type: "numeric"
    });
```

