Yeesh, amazing how much you can forget in three months. I went digging back to July and I'm missing some of the commits I remember doing so I think this got squashed when I was resolving all the rebase conflicts. The correct result is written to memory in `R_ARM_CALL.value` but `Relocation.relocate()` would be overwriting the same location with 0x1, for all `R_ARM_CALL` (and equivalent) relocs. 

@Phat3, do you have test binaries handy? I can't check it right now but I'm fairly certain you can also remove the memory write at [line 69](https://github.com/Phat3/cle/blob/780dfdc78af1d7dd1e66a29ca8bf9faf123cbbfb/cle/backends/elf/relocation/arm.py#L69). That should be taken care of by [Relocation.relocate()](https://github.com/angr/cle/blob/bc7443b2c342c22fd549d8a7ba2fc85677bd91a2/cle/backends/relocation.py#L113).

